From gem5/configs/common/Options.py

The default cache sizes for gem5 are:
L1_Instruction: size 32kB
L1_Data:        size 64kB
L2 Cache:       size 2MB


These sizes can be changed on the command line when running gem5:

build/X86/gem5.opt configs/example.se.py --caches --l2cache --l1i_size="8kB"
--l1d_size="16kB" --l2_size="64kB" -c
tests/test-progs/cprogs/x86executables/<name>


Default associativity:
L1 Inst Assoc: 2
L1 Data Assoc: 2
L2 Assoc:      8


